<section xml:id="list-algorithms-iterators_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>forward iterator:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>forward iterator</h>
          </idx> An iterator that allows traversal of a container in a forward direction, accessing elements one by one.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>random access iterator:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>random access iterator</h>
          </idx> An iterator that allows direct access to any element in a container, using subscripting (<pf>[]</pf>) or arithmetic operations.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>reverse iterator:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>reverse iterator</h>
          </idx> An iterator that allows traversal of a container in a reverse direction, accessing elements one by one.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>